pT4 - Tumor of any size that invades mediastinum/heart/great vessels/trachea/esophagus/vertebral body/carina or with separate tumor nodule(s) in same lobe or with malignant pleural effusion

pT3 - Tumor of any size that directly invades chest wall/diaphragm/mediastinal/pleura/parietal pericardium/main bronchus(less than 2cmdistal to carina without involement)/associated with atelectasis or obstructive pneumonitis
pT2 - Tumor with greater than 3cm in greastest dimension or involves main bronchus or 2cm/more distal to carina or invades visceral pleura or associated with atelectasis/obstructive pneumonitis
pT1 - Tumor 3cm or less in greatest dimension surrounded by lung or visceral pleura without bronchoscopic evidence of invasion more proximal than lobar bronchus
pTX - Cannot be assessed or tumor proven by presence of malignant cells in sputum or bronchial washings but not visualized by imaging or bronchoscopy
pT4b - Tumor penetrates the visceral peritoneum
pT4a - Tumor directly invades other organs or structures
pT4 - Tumor directly invades adjacent structures
pT3c/d - Tumor invades through muscularis propria into subserosa or nonperitonealized pericolic or perirectal soft tissues - invades greater than 5mm beyond border of muscularis propria
pT3a/b - Tumor invades through muscularis propria into subserosa or nonperitonealized pericolic or perirectal soft tissues - invades 5mm or less beyond border of muscularis propria
pT3 - Tumor invades through muscularis propria into subserosa or nonperitonealized pericolic or perirectal soft tissues
pTis - Carcinoma in situ - invasion of lamina propria
pTis - Carcinoma in situ - intraepithelial (no invasion)
pT4b - Melanoma greater than 4mm in thickness with ulceration
pT4a - Melanoma greater than 4mm in thickness with no ulceration
pT4 - Melanoma greater than 4mm in thickness with or without ulceration
pT4 - Invasion of bladder and/or rectum
pT2b - Unilateral and involves more than one half of one side but not both
pT2a - Unilateral and involves one half of one side or less
pT4 - Tumor involves celiac axis or superior mesentric artery
